{
  "name": "5 \u00b7 Wiki Maintenance (weekly, manual)",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "description": "Weekly (Friday) wiki maintenance. Replaces the wiki_lint recurring task previously embedded in EOD Phase 4. Manually triggered so daily EOD stays lean. Consumes wiki-candidates.md from hook contributions, refreshes SharePoint cache, rebuilds the wiki index (dashboard JSON + human-readable wiki-index.md), runs audit, proposes action.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run weekly wiki maintenance. This replaces the wiki_lint recurring task formerly embedded in EOD Phase 4. Manual trigger only \u2014 usually Friday. IMPORTANT: Richard is in Pacific Time (America/Los_Angeles). Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date +%Y-%m-%d` for today's PT date. --- ## PHASE 1: Consume wiki-candidates.md Read ~/shared/context/intake/wiki-candidates.md. For each contribution from the past 7 days:\n1. Dedupe by signal similarity + proposed slug.\n2. Group related signals \u2014 if multiple hooks (am-auto, eod, wbr-callouts, session-summary) flagged the same topic in the same week, that's a strong signal.\n3. Cross-reference against ~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/wiki-index.md to check if the proposed article (or similar) already exists.\n4. Propose the top 3-5 candidates to ~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/review-queue.md with: signal summary, evidence (which hooks flagged it), and action (new article / enrich existing / skip with reason).\n5. Archive processed entries: move consumed lines from wiki-candidates.md to ~/shared/context/intake/archive/wiki-candidates-YYYY-WNN.md. ## PHASE 2: Refresh SharePoint cache + rebuild index Before auditing, refresh the SharePoint snapshot and regenerate the index. The builder writes both the dashboard JSON AND _meta/wiki-index.md from one scan, so nothing has to be edited by hand. 1. For each category folder under Documents/Artifacts/ (testing, strategy, markets, operations, reporting, research, _meta): call `sharepoint_list_files(libraryName=\"Documents\", folderPath=f\"Artifacts/{cat}\", top=200)`.\n2. For each returned .docx: capture Name (strip .docx for stem), Path, Modified, Size.\n3. Write to `~/shared/dashboards/data/sharepoint-artifacts.json` with schema: `{\"generated\": ISO, \"artifacts\": [{\"stem\", \"category\", \"path\", \"modified\", \"size\"}, ...]}`.\n4. Run `python3 ~/shared/dashboards/build-wiki-index.py`. This regenerates `data/wiki-search-index.json` (for the dashboard) AND `_meta/wiki-index.md` (for humans and agents). Expected output lines: `SharePoint: N published / M local-only / K published-stale` and `Wiki index .md: ...`.\n5. Sanity-check the published/stale/local-only counts against your expectations. Unexpected zeros mean the SharePoint crawl failed \u2014 check cache file. ## PHASE 3: Wiki lint audit With a fresh index in hand, run the audit checks:\n1. Orphan scan: `wiki-index.md` is auto-generated now \u2014 orphans can only exist as files that should have been indexed but weren't. Compare `find shared/wiki/agent-created -name '*.md'` count (minus archive/reviews/_meta/intake/kiro-steering) against the Summary total in `wiki-index.md`.\n2. Stale content: articles past their update-trigger window. Use doc-type bucket rules once the 4-bucket vocabulary is active (see _meta/pending-vocabulary-update.md). Until then, flag articles with `updated` > 90 days and `foundational: true` not set.\n3. Broken cross-refs: relative links in articles that resolve to missing files.\n4. Missing frontmatter: articles without required fields (title, status, audience, owner).\n5. SharePoint-stale: read `sharepoint.stale` count from `data/wiki-search-index.json`. Each stale doc is a candidate for a re-push.\n6. Local-only REVIEW articles: docs with `status: REVIEW` but `published: false` are ready-to-publish but haven't been pushed. Flag for Richard's decision.\n7. Signal-based freshness: query DuckDB `signals.wiki_candidates` view. For topics with strong signal but no matching article, add to wiki-candidates pipeline.\n8. Blackboard health check: count articles with `.state.json` sidecars vs without. Build is deferred until 2026-04-30 \u2014 status check only, no nag posture. Write results to `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/health-YYYY-MM-DD.md` and `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/audit-YYYY-MM-DD.md`. ## PHASE 4: Idea sourcing from signals Query `signals.wiki_candidates` view. For topics with strong multi-channel signal but no matching article, add as candidates to review-queue.md. ## PHASE 5: Roadmap update Update `~/shared/wiki/agent-created/_meta/roadmap.md` Queued section with new proposals from Phases 1 and 4. Mark completed items (from last week's pipeline) as Done. ## PHASE 6: Report Report summary to Richard:\n- Candidates consumed: N lines processed, X promoted to review-queue, Y deduplicated.\n- SharePoint sync: N published, M local-only, K stale (needs re-push).\n- Audit results: N healthy, N stale (content-age), N orphaned, N broken refs.\n- New ideas from signals: top 3 with evidence.\n- Action items for Richard: which proposals need his review this week. If `wiki-candidates.md` is empty AND the audit finds no issues AND SharePoint has no stale docs, report `\ud83d\udcda Wiki maintenance: nothing to do this week.` and stop \u2014 don't write empty audit files. --- KILL CONDITION: 2026-06-01. If after 6 weekly runs the wiki-candidates queue has produced <3 articles that Richard chose to promote, the distributed-contribution model isn't producing signal worth the hook overhead. Revert hook contributions and delete wiki-candidates.md. Keep or kill \u2014 document the decision in `~/shared/context/intake/session-log.md`."
  }
}